excerpt: Museum featuring over 45,000 works covering 6,000 years plus films, music, lectures & a restaurant.
detail_description: The Cleveland Museum of Art, established in 1916, is a popular destination in Ohio, attracting over half a billion visitors annually. The museum boasts an impressive collection of nearly 45,000 artifacts spanning 6,000 years. Its exhibits are elegantly displayed in chronological order, showcasing the evolution of renowned artists throughout history. Additionally, the museum offers a special play area for children and hosts various events and exhibits.
name: The Cleveland Museum of Art

excerpt: Iconic music-minded museum loaded with pop-culture memorabilia, artifacts, instruments & a jukebox.
detail_description: The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame is a museum dedicated to the history of rock and roll. It features displays on the music, the performers, and the industry. The museum is located in Cleveland, Ohio.
name: Rock & Roll Hall of Fame

excerpt: Grand, bustling public market from 1912 featuring vendors for meat, produce, bread & hot food.
detail_description: West Side Market, established in 1912, is a vibrant and historic public market offering a wide array of goods such as meat, produce, bread, and hot food. The market originally had 109 stalls with additional storage added later. Many of the stalls are still operated by families who have been there since its opening, while others are run by vendors from various parts of the world.
name: West Side Market

excerpt: All-seasons living museum with a greenhouse, a conservatory, outdoor gardens & an education center.
detail_description: Nestled in the University Circle near other cultural attractions, Cleveland Botanical Garden is a captivating all-seasons living museum spanning 10 acres. The Eleanor Armstrong Smith Glasshouse is a highlight, featuring peculiar desert and rainforest plants alongside hundreds of butterflies, birds, and reptiles. Families can also explore the Hershey Children's Garden for nature play activities. The garden boasts diverse landscapes including herb, Japanese, rose, and topiary gardens as well as a greenhouse and conservatory.
name: Cleveland Botanical Garden

excerpt: Animal exhibits, a simulated rainforest, an interactive kids section, a gift shop & restaurants.
detail_description: Cleveland Metroparks Zoo is a sprawling wildlife sanctuary with over 3,000 animals from 600 species. The zoo offers interactive experiences like giraffe and lorikeet feedings, camel rides, and overnight programs in safari tents. Visitors can explore distinct areas of the zoo featuring favorites such as Elephant Crossing and a carousel. Despite its location near downtown Cleveland, the hilly landscape creates an immersive experience away from the city's industrial surroundings.
name: Cleveland Metroparks Zoo

excerpt: House used in "A Christmas Story" film, now a museum with a replicated interior & film memorabilia.
detail_description: The House from A Christmas Story, located in Cleveland, Ohio, is a 19th-century Victorian home that was used for exterior shots in the classic Christmas movie. It has been transformed into a museum and cafe where visitors can explore the replicated interior and view film memorabilia. The house offers fans of the movie an opportunity to step inside Ralphie's iconic home and relive favorite moments from the film.
name: House from A Christmas Story

excerpt: Planetarium & museum focusing on local prehistoric discoveries, fossils & geological specimens.
detail_description: The Cleveland Museum of Natural History is a treasure trove for anyone fascinated by the wonders of our planet. Nestled just five miles from downtown Cleveland in University Circle, this museum has been captivating visitors since its inception in 1920. With an exciting array of offerings including immersive 3D films and engaging planetarium shows, it caters to science enthusiasts of all ages. The museum is currently undergoing a remarkable $150 million renovation that aims to enhance its facilities and exhibits significantly.
name: Cleveland Museum of Natural History
address: 1 Wade Oval Dr, Cleveland, OH 44106, USA

excerpt: Kid-friendly venue with interactive exhibits, plus a giant-screen movie theater & steamship tours.
detail_description: Great Lakes Science Center is a must-visit, family-friendly venue in Downtown Cleveland. It offers interactive exhibits, a giant-screen movie theater, and steamship tours. The Science Store in the main lobby is accessible without paying admission and features astronaut ice cream, NASA apparel, STEM gifts, and solar eclipse safety glasses. The center was a finalist for Best Science Museum in the 2022 USA Today 10Best Readers Choice travel award contest.
name: Great Lakes Science Center

excerpt: Tranquil burial place of billionaire John D. Rockefeller & former president James A. Garfield.
detail_description: Lake View Cemetery, established in 1869, is a serene burial ground that also serves as a picturesque destination for visitors. The landscape features stunning gardens inspired by European designs and offers dramatic views, winding pathways, and historic structures. Notable attractions include the James A. Garfield Memorial, Wade Memorial Chapel, the Haserot angel sculpture, and Daffodil Hill in spring. This tranquil setting provides an opportunity to connect with nature and beauty while paying homage to prominent figures like billionaire John D.
name: Lake View Cemetery

excerpt: Contemporary art, educational programs & performances presented in an edgy steel-paneled structure.
detail_description: The Museum of Contemporary Art Cleveland, also known as moCa, stands out with its ever-changing exhibitions from present-day artists. The museum's edgy steel-paneled structure houses thought-provoking and dynamic displays that celebrate modern art in all its forms. In addition to showcasing over 2,000 artists, moCa offers educational programs and performances within its unique architectural setting. Visitors can expect a refreshing experience with each visit as they explore the diverse range of contemporary works on display.
name: Museum of Contemporary Art Cleveland

excerpt: Interactive marine exhibits, including a walk-through experience & a mock research vessel.
detail_description: The Greater Cleveland Aquarium offers an immersive experience for visitors of all ages, with over fifty exhibits spread across eight galleries. Children can enjoy interactive marine displays, including a walk-through experience and a mock research vessel. The Touch Pool in the Coastal Boardwalk gallery allows kids to come face to face with and touch stingrays, while older children can be surrounded by sharks and other sea creatures in the underwater Sea Tube.
name: Greater Cleveland Aquarium

excerpt: Open for tours from May 1 to September 30, this World War II-era sub honors fallen submariners.
detail_description: The USS Cod Submarine Memorial in Cleveland, Ohio is a World War II-era submarine that pays tribute to fallen submariners. It is open for tours from May 1 to September 30 and is listed as one of the area's National Historic Landmarks. The submarine is maintained in its original condition, allowing visitors to experience its history firsthand by using the original hatchways and ladders during their tour.
name: USS Cod Submarine Memorial
address: 1201 N Marginal Rd, Cleveland, OH 44114, USA

excerpt: Cleveland is a city in the U.S. state of Ohio and the county seat of Cuyahoga County. Located along the southern shore of Lake Erie, it is situated across the Canada–U.S. maritime border and approximately 60 mi west of the Ohio-Pennsylvania state border. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Cleveland, a city in Ohio, is located on the southern shore of Lake Erie and is known for its annual -X Indoor Amusement Park that offers fair food and thrilling rides. The park has become a tradition in northeastern Ohio, drawing visitors to enjoy the unique country fair experience. Additionally, Cleveland is home to Brookside Reservation, a Cleveland Metropark featuring athletic fields and the Cleveland Metroparks Zoo. The reservation offers the 2.
name: Cleveland

excerpt: The Flats is a redeveloped area on the banks of the Cuyahoga River, known for its happening nightlife, with edgy bars and clubs hosting live music, comedy and drag shows. The party vibe extends to patios and beer gardens nearby, while dining options include gourmet taco joints and hip cafes. A popular walkway lines the west bank of the waterfront, and water taxis take people from one side of the river to the other.
detail_description: The Flats is a revitalized area along the Cuyahoga River, offering a vibrant nightlife scene with trendy bars and clubs featuring live entertainment. Visitors can enjoy various dining options including gourmet taco spots and stylish cafes. The west bank of the waterfront boasts a popular walkway, while water taxis provide convenient transportation across the river. This district has undergone significant urban renewal, transforming former industrial zones into an entertainment-focused waterfront section and introducing new sports stadiums to the city.
name: The Flats

excerpt: Gaming venue with slots, table games, live music & several restaurants, including a buffet.
detail_description: Nestled in the iconic Higbee Building in Public Square, Jack Cleveland Casino is a vibrant gaming destination that promises an unforgettable night out. Spanning over 100,000 square feet, this lively venue features an impressive array of entertainment options including more than 500 slot machines and 100 table games, alongside 30 poker tables for those looking to test their skills.
name: JACK Cleveland Casino

excerpt: Cleveland Guardians home field with a mezzanine-level kids' club, concessions & youth workshops.
detail_description: Progressive Field, the vibrant home of the Cleveland Guardians, is a fantastic destination for families and baseball enthusiasts alike. This impressive stadium not only accommodates over 35,000 fans but also features a delightful Family Deck designed specifically for parents and their little ones. Here, you'll find an inviting lounge area alongside family-friendly concessions and the Kids Clubhouse—an interactive space brimming with engaging activities to keep children entertained.
name: Progressive Field

excerpt: Contemporary art & photography museum, plus events, in an expanded 1924 railroad substation.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Ohio City neighborhood, Transformer Station is a unique contemporary art and photography museum that breathes new life into a historic 1924 railroad substation. Originally built to power the Detroit Avenue Streetcar Line, this architectural gem has been transformed into a cultural hub since its renovation in 2010. Open to the public from Wednesday to Sunday, it offers free access to an array of exhibitions featuring both emerging and mid-career artists with a strong focus on photography and social justice themes.
name: Transformer Station

excerpt: Soaring, ornate indoor mall, opened in 1890, today housing the Hyatt hotel, shops & restaurants.
detail_description: The Arcade, also known as the Old Arcade, is a magnificent indoor mall in downtown Cleveland that opened its doors in 1890. It holds the distinction of being America's first indoor shopping center and was financed by prominent businessmen including John D. Rockefeller. The design of the Arcade was inspired by Milan's Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II and it is often referred to as the Crystal Palace. In addition to housing shops and restaurants, it also accommodates the Hyatt hotel.
name: The Arcade

excerpt: Park on Lake Erie featuring a yacht club, beaches, a fishing pier, picnic areas & more.
detail_description: Edgewater Park is a picturesque park located on the shores of Lake Erie, forming part of the Cleveland Metroparks Lakefront Reservation. It boasts 9,000 feet of shoreline and features attractions such as Edgewater Beach, Perkins Beach, a Marina and Yacht Club. The park offers various activities including biking, boating, paddle sports, picnicking and fishing. Visitors can also enjoy amenities like picnic tables, restrooms and trail access.
name: Edgewater Park

excerpt: Iconic microbrewery with house suds, an updated American menu, free tours & a patio.
detail_description: Great Lakes Brewing Company is a renowned microbrewery in Ohio City, offering house suds and an updated American menu. The brewery's store provides a variety of traditional items, making it a great spot for last-minute gift shopping. In addition to its brewpub and seven-barrel brewhouse, the company has become a Cleveland landmark with its all-wood interior and home-grown beer.
name: Great Lakes Brewing Company
